Url.Title: Setting login and language preferences
Url.Abstract: Setting login and language preferences The Self-Service Portal can remember certain preferences you set on the login page, even after you log out of the application and close your browser.

Url.Title: Viewing information about your mobile device or computer
Url.Abstract: Viewing information about your mobile device or computer You can view details about the current status of your mobile device or computer.

Url.Title: Sending a message to your mobile device or computer
Url.Abstract: Sending a message to your mobile device or computer If you need to communicate something to the person who is currently using your mobile device or computer, you can send a message for the user to read.

Url.Title: Locking your mobile device or OS X computer
Url.Abstract: Locking your mobile device or OS X computer You can issue a command to remotely lock a mobile device, or an OS X computer running version 10.10 and higher, making it unusable until the correct passcode or password is entered locally.

Url.Title: Clearing the passcode on your mobile device
Url.Abstract: Clearing the passcode on your mobile device You can issue a command to remotely clear the existing passcode on your mobile device. With Android devices, you also have the option to set a new passcode of your choice.

Url.Title: Setting the passcode on your Android device
Url.Abstract: Setting the passcode on your Android device You can issue a command to remotely set a new passcode on your Android device.

Url.Title: Erasing your mobile device or OS X computer
Url.Abstract: Erasing your mobile device or OS X computer You can issue a command to remotely erase a mobile device or an OS X computer running version 10.10 and higher.
